What you need to know:

Bt-cotton, a crop commercialised in 15 countries over the last 20 years, has undergone rigorous evaluation in different agro-ecological zones in the country where conventional cotton varieties are normally grown.Among the concerns over GM crops are safety of inserted genetic elements, short and long-term direct health effects (toxicity), and possibility to provoke allergic reactions as well as alterations in food nutritional and compositional properties in diverse uses.Once approved by the authority, the GMO products are clearly labelled for consumer information and ease of traceability.If any unintended effect attributed to the approved GMO is noted, the product shall be recalled from the market immediately.